generateConstantStrings

void generateConstantStrings()
write the constant strings.

This is:

  • One big character block in the code segment, containing all the constant strings, always terminated with a Null character.
  • A fake character-array object in the data segment, pointing to this block.
  • Many fake String objects in the data segment, pointing (with offset) into the character array.
  • An 'init_constant_strings' routine to set up the pointers.

layoutSegments

void layoutSegments()
Assign segment numbers to the methods.

The segment layout tries to make sure that the code in one segment cannot exceed 32K. Segment 1 contains the kernel routines, segment 2 the constant strings, methods are found in segments starting with number 3.

The layout is based on heuristic assumptions on the expansion factor from bytecode to native code.

segmentOneLabels

java.util.Vector segmentOneLabels()
Collect the segment-1 labels. The method returns a Vector containing all global labels from code segment 1. These are the fixed labels from the invariant part of the code generator plus the global labels from file 'kernel.asm' (those with a colon).

segmentTwoLabels

java.util.Vector segmentTwoLabels()
Collect the segment-2 labels. The method returns a Vector containing all global labels from code segment 2. These are the labels for the constant strings.
